      <T n="image" p="InEP18\UI\Tutorial\EP18_Lesson_FamilyRecipes_Slide1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:01ef7ed17acdcab7</T>
      <T n="text">0x419C3E21<!--Remember that unbeatable grilled cheese sandwich a certain someone always used to make for you as a kid? That was probably a <b><font color='#199C2C'>Family Recipe</font></b>!\n\nSims will experience certain moments throughout their life that will unlock <b><font color='#199C2C'>Special Touches</font></b> that can enhance a meal with extraordinary effects! These can be applied to any <b><font color='#199C2C'>Cooking</font></b> recipe of your choosing by doing the Create New Family Recipe interaction on a Stove, Fridge or the new <b><font color='#199C2C'>Grammy's Family Recipes</font></b> Cookbook. There can only be one Family Recipe that uses a certain Special Touch at the same time.--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP18\UI\Tutorial\EP18_Lesson_FamilyRecipes_Slide2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:01ef7ed17acdcab4</T>
      <T n="text">0x191EBECC<!--During recipe creation, select which recipe you want to alter and choose a <b><font color='#199C2C'>Special Touch</font></b> to apply and add a <b><font color='#199C2C'>Secret Ingredient</font></b>. You can then name your Family Recipe and cook it! The Special Touch will add effects to the meal for the lucky consumer to benefit from!\n\nYour Sim can also <b><font color='#199C2C'>pass on</font></b> this Family Recipe to another Sim in your household, provided they are on good terms and have the necessary Cooking skills! This can be done through the Teach Family Recipes interaction on any Stove, Fridge, or Cookbook.--></T>
    </U>
